      • resolveSymbol

        protected SymbolEntry resolveSymbol(java.util.List<TId> path)
        Find the entry in the symbol table that defines the specified id. The id is the last id on the specified path. Each id in the path represents the id of an enclosing scope. The current scope is first searched, and if the path is not found relative to the current scope, then the global scope is searched. Return null if not found.

      • resolveForwardReferences

        protected void resolveForwardReferences(DeclaredEntry entry)
        Beginning with the current scope, and progressing outward, attempt to resolve the unresolved references that are attached to each scope. This method should be called after each name declaration is processed.
